  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct intended for lumbar spinal fixation in skeletally mature patients. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors are assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below the required credibility level due to a single test condition being evaluated. The intended use scope — quasi-static compressive-bending loads applied to a two-level L4-S1 pedicle screw-rod construct in a 5.5 mm rod configuration — is described in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes. Decision: Accepted at Medium assurance level with model risk level 3.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/nagaraja-f1717-compression-bending-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/nagaraja-fea-predicts-f1717-construct-stiffness-and-yield",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/nagaraja-pedicle-screw-fea-ensemble-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-experimental-n11-lab1",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-experimental-n11-lab2"
  ],
